CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>select farmers.name, crops.crop_name, harvest.quantity from farmers join crops on farmers.id = crops.farmer_id join harvest on crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>SELECT crops.crop_name, fields.field_name, fields.field_size FROM crops JOIN fields ON crops.crop_id = fields.crop_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>SELECT farmers.name, fields.field_name, harvest.quantity FROM farmers JOIN crops ON farmers.id = crops.farmer_id JOIN fields ON crops.crop_id = fields.crop_id JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))</t><stat>SELECT farmers.name, fields.field_name, harvest.quantity FROM farmers JOIN crops ON farmers.id = crops.farmer_id JOIN fields ON crops.crop_id = fields.crop_id JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>SELECT farmers.name, round(avg(harvest.quantity), 2) as avg_quantity FROM farmers JOIN crops ON farmers.id = crops.farmer_id JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id GROUP BY farmers.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>select farmers.name, round(avg(harvest.quantity), 2) as avg_quantity from farmers join crops on farmers.id = crops.farmer_id join harvest on crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id group by farmers.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>SELECT crop_type, sum(quantity) as total_quantity FROM crops JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id GROUP BY crop_type</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>select crop_type, sum(quantity) as total_quantity from crops join harvest on crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id group by crop_type</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))</t><stat>SELECT crops.crop_name, sum(harvest.quantity) as total_quantity FROM crops JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id GROUP BY crops.crop_name</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE farmers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, location VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE crops (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(50), crop_type VARCHAR(50), farmer_id INT REFERENCES farmers(id))

CREATE TABLE harvest (harvest_id INT PRIMARY KEY, harvest_date DATE, quantity INT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))</t><stat>SELECT crops.crop_name, max(harvest.quantity) as max_quantity FROM crops JOIN harvest ON crops.crop_id = harvest.crop_id GROUP BY crops.crop_name</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE fields (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(50), field_size FLOAT, crop_id INT REFERENCES crops(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crop (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), growing_season VARCHAR(50), yield_per_acre FLOAT)</t><stat>SELECT farm.id, field.size FROM farm JOIN field ON farm.id = field.farm_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farmer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crop (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), growing_season VARCHAR(50), yield_per_acre FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)</t><stat>SELECT farm.id, field.size FROM farm JOIN field ON farm.id = field.farm_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS machinery (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), condition VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farm (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100), established_date DATE)</t><stat>select farm.id, field.size from farm join field on farm.id = field.farm_id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farm (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100), established_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farmer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crop (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), growing_season VARCHAR(50), yield_per_acre FLOAT)</t><stat>SELECT crop.name, field.soil_type FROM crop JOIN field ON crop.id = field.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farm (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100), established_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farmer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS machinery (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), condition VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>SELECT farmer.name, farm.location FROM farmer JOIN farm ON farmer.id = farm.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS machinery (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), condition VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crop (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), growing_season VARCHAR(50), yield_per_acre FLOAT)</t><stat>SELECT farm.name, machinery.type FROM farm JOIN machinery ON farm.id = machinery.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS field (id INT PRIMARY KEY, farm_id INT, size FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (farm_id) REFERENCES farm(id) ON DELETE CASCADE)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crop (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), growing_season VARCHAR(50), yield_per_acre FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS farm (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(100), established_date DATE)</t><stat>select farmer.name, crop.type from farmer join crop on farmer.id = crop.id</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS machinery (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), type VARCHAR(50), condition VARCHAR(50))
